The paper deals with resource provisioning and task scheduling in distributed computing systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The proposed approach involves a deep learning architecture, which suggests the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of forecasting models and adaptive data-reduction algorithms suggests the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes a communication-efficient data collection mechanism, which may also place it in the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
